FuncDef: The uninstall-module command uninstalls a specified module file online. The uninstall-module command uninstalls a specified module file online.

ParaDef.Info:
Specifies the name of the module file to be uninstalled.
The value is a string of 5 to 63 case-sensitive characters, spaces not supported.

Specifies that all module files need to be uninstalled.
-

Examples: This will uninstall the xxxxxx.MOD module. Are you sure? [Y/N]:Y
Warning: This will uninstall all the module. Continue? [Y/N]:y
ExtraInfo: This command is used to uninstall a running module from the system. The display module-information command displays whether a specified module has been uninstalled in the system.
